WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.420
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.420 --> 00:00:04.440
How far would you go to
charge your cell phone

00:00:04.440 --> 00:00:07.110
if you had no electricity?

00:00:07.110 --> 00:00:10.505
Would you walk for hours?

00:00:10.505 --> 00:00:11.005
Miles?

00:00:13.610 --> 00:00:16.610
That's what millions of people
across sub-Saharan Africa

00:00:16.610 --> 00:00:19.920
do every day simply to
charge their phones.

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:22.275
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:22.275 --> 00:00:25.330
LAURA LING: I'm Here in Tanzania
because sub-Saharan Africa

00:00:25.330 --> 00:00:28.650
is experiencing a
major energy crisis.

00:00:28.650 --> 00:00:31.850
Modern-day Africa has been
transformed by cell phones,

00:00:31.850 --> 00:00:34.910
but the infrastructure needed
to charge those phones,

00:00:34.910 --> 00:00:38.650
and to power sub-Saharan Africa
in general, just isn't there.

00:00:38.650 --> 00:00:41.912
And it's leaving hundreds of
millions of people in the dark.

00:00:41.912 --> 00:00:44.870
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:44.870 --> 00:00:48.250
In the village of Mkuranga,
I immediately felt welcomed.

00:00:48.250 --> 00:00:51.030
Since most people don't have
electricity in their homes,

00:00:51.030 --> 00:00:54.540
they go to charging stations
to power their phones.

00:00:54.540 --> 00:00:57.150
Recho Mango, a health care
provider at the local clinic,

00:00:57.150 --> 00:00:59.940
was picking up her cellphone
that she paid roughly $0.20

00:00:59.940 --> 00:01:01.028
to charge.

00:01:01.028 --> 00:01:02.432
Hi, I'm Laura.

00:01:02.432 --> 00:01:03.593
Nice to meet you.

00:01:03.593 --> 00:01:04.280
RECHO MENGO: Nice to meet you.

00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:06.350
LAURA LING: She took me to her
clinic's maternity ward, which

00:01:06.350 --> 00:01:07.340
has no power.

00:01:07.340 --> 00:01:08.640
So this is the clinic?

00:01:08.640 --> 00:01:10.292
RECHO MENGO: Yeah,
this is the clinic.

00:01:20.190 --> 00:01:23.395
LAURA LING: Do you often have
to deliver babies in the dark

00:01:23.395 --> 00:01:24.436
because there's no light?

00:01:28.670 --> 00:01:31.160
Vital immunizations for
mothers and children

00:01:31.160 --> 00:01:33.785
are kept cool by gas
from a propane tank.

00:01:39.980 --> 00:01:42.040
It's getting dark
out, and Recho is

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:44.790
about to see a client who
is in her third trimester

00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:45.660
of pregnancy.

00:01:45.660 --> 00:01:48.090
And she could give
birth at any moment.

00:01:48.090 --> 00:01:50.270
So Recho basically
has to do whatever

00:01:50.270 --> 00:01:51.890
she can just make it work.

00:02:21.690 --> 00:02:23.690
According to the World
Health Organization,

00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:26.390
women in developing
countries such as Tanzania

00:02:26.390 --> 00:02:29.280
are dying every 90
seconds from complications

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:32.300
during pregnancy or childbirth.

00:02:32.300 --> 00:02:35.500
Would having adequate
light save lives?

00:02:42.990 --> 00:02:45.360
While a few homes in
this town are connected

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:47.590
to an electrical grid,
they often experience

00:02:47.590 --> 00:02:50.880
frequent blackouts, sometimes
lasting up to 48 hours.

00:02:50.880 --> 00:02:53.400
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:53.900 --> 00:02:57.490
18-year-old Hussein Mwende
has lived his entire life

00:02:57.490 --> 00:03:00.660
without ever having
electricity in his home.

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:02.880
What you want to be
when you grow up?

00:03:37.444 --> 00:03:40.130
It sounds extremely
difficult. Do

00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:41.855
you ever feel like giving up?

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:56.990
Mkuranga is typical of many
villages across Tanzania.

00:03:56.990 --> 00:03:59.462
Just a few hours away is
Tanzania's largest city,

00:03:59.462 --> 00:04:00.045
Dar es Salaam.

00:04:03.420 --> 00:04:06.040
It might seem surprising,
but Africa has the world's

00:04:06.040 --> 00:04:09.620
fastest-growing middle class.

00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:12.365
While there still is a long
way to go, signs of development

00:04:12.365 --> 00:04:14.870
are all around.

