LAURA LING: There's
a blackout right now.

00:04:45.705 --> 00:04:46.580
You have a generator.

00:04:46.580 --> 00:04:49.241
That's why we hear this
little buzz in the air.

00:04:49.241 --> 00:04:50.366
MERCY KITOMARI: Yeah, yeah.

00:04:50.366 --> 00:04:51.067
And it's often.

00:04:51.067 --> 00:04:53.150
LAURA LING: It seems
extremely challenging to have

00:04:53.150 --> 00:04:58.120
this kind of business in a
country with so many blackouts.

00:04:58.120 --> 00:05:00.480
MERCY KITOMARI: It
does slow you down.

00:05:00.480 --> 00:05:03.250
When power cuts off, the
first thing is the freezers.

00:05:03.250 --> 00:05:04.015
You freak out.

00:05:04.015 --> 00:05:05.710
I started thinking, oh, shit.

00:05:05.710 --> 00:05:07.160
Need to hire a generator.

00:05:07.160 --> 00:05:09.552
You hire a car to bring it.

00:05:09.552 --> 00:05:12.220
You hire a crane to lift it.

00:05:12.220 --> 00:05:14.422
And for the generator,
they charge you per hour.

00:05:14.422 --> 00:05:15.880
LAURA LING: So it's
very expensive.

00:05:15.880 --> 00:05:16.713
MERCY KITOMARI: Yes.

00:05:16.713 --> 00:05:19.080
LAURA LING: And meanwhile,
your gelato is melting.

00:05:19.080 --> 00:05:20.020
MERCY KITOMARI: Yeah.

00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:21.436
LAURA LING: Is it
worth it to you?

00:05:21.436 --> 00:05:22.510
MERCY KITOMARI: It is.

00:05:22.510 --> 00:05:24.050
It has been worth it.

00:05:24.050 --> 00:05:26.560
It's been super challenging.

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:27.865
Super, super challenging.

00:05:27.865 --> 00:05:32.100
But every day, there's progress.

00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:33.990
LAURA LING: Mercy
relies on social media

00:05:33.990 --> 00:05:35.220
to build her business.

00:05:35.220 --> 00:05:37.640
In many ways, her
entrepreneurial spirit

00:05:37.640 --> 00:05:39.950
represents Africa's
enormous potential.

00:05:39.950 --> 00:05:44.400
But energy issues may determine
how bright that future will be.

00:05:44.400 --> 00:05:46.650
MERCY KITOMARI: I love my
country, don't get me wrong.

00:05:46.650 --> 00:05:49.684
But there's still a
lot of work to be done.

