00:06:46.380 --> 00:06:48.560
It seems strange and
a little unsettling

00:06:48.560 --> 00:06:52.175
to be in near total darkness
that was beyond my control.

00:06:52.175 --> 00:06:55.570
But those around me
didn't seem fazed.

00:06:55.570 --> 00:06:58.930
This is life as normal here,
and in pretty much the rest

00:06:58.930 --> 00:07:00.930
of sub-Saharan Africa.

00:07:00.930 --> 00:07:03.460
Thinking back on
the people I'd met,

00:07:03.460 --> 00:07:06.910
they were making it
work despite challenges.

00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:09.380
And if power never
arrives, I'm sure they'll

00:07:09.380 --> 00:07:11.920
keep plugging away, determined
to make a better life

00:07:11.920 --> 00:07:14.320
for themselves and for others.

00:07:14.320 --> 00:07:18.880
But charging stations and
generators will only go so far.

00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:21.020
These are some of the
friendliest and supportive

00:07:21.020 --> 00:07:22.830
people I've ever met.

00:07:22.830 --> 00:07:25.660
They deserve better,
and I wish them well.

